<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: 6502 Programmable Logic Array]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10867&amp;p=123523#p123523"><![CDATA[
The lookup table has been fully decoded, and as you've noticed, it's part of Visual6502. Just click one by one through the columns of the PLA to get the names they've assigned.<br />Alternatively, you can dig around on their site (google:<tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">site:visual6502.org pla</tt>) and get to this page: <a href="http://visual6502.org/wiki/index.php?title=6507_Decode_ROM" class="postlink">visual6502wiki:6507 Decode ROM</a> or <a href="http://visual6502.org/wiki/index.php?title=650X_Schematic_Notes" class="postlink">visual6502wiki:650X Schematic Notes</a><br /><br />Sometimes the signals are something intelligible, such as &quot;node: 1601 op-sty/cpy-mem&quot;, but as often they're something cryptic like &quot;node: 1031 op-T3-stack/bit/jmp&quot; which tells you &quot;when&quot; but not anything else particularly useful. Getting from this &quot;branch of tree&quot; level view up to the forest requires more than just looking at the node names and when they fire.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Wed Jan 08, 2014 7:26 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
